text: Elections to Epping Forest Council were held on 6 May 1999. One third of the council was up for election and the council stayed under no overall control. Overall turnout was 29%. After the election, the composition of the council was *Conservative 19 *Liberal Democrat 15 *Labour 14 *Residents 7 *Independent 3 *Others 1 ==Election result== ==Ward results== ==References== *1999 Epping Forest election result *Ward results 1999 Category:1999 English local elections Category:1990s in Essex
